exec: pm.test("The welcome information api status test.", function() {
pm.test("The welcome information api body test.", function() {

query.description: The name of the moon searching for. The API will return all moons whose name contains it.
The index of the moon searching for. The API will return the moon at the index.

request.description:
# Moon

This API is used to request the data of moons. It depends on the GET method, and it contains two parameters. Both parameters ignore case.

The request has to contain one of the above parameters at least.

query.description: The name of the planet searching for. The API will return all planets whose name contains it.
The index of the planet searching for. The API will return the planet at the index.

request.description:
# Planet

This API provides data of all planets. It contains 13 parameters, and the request needs to have at least one of them.

The request has to contain one of the above parameters at least.

query.description: The index of the star searching for. The API will return the star at the index.
The name of the star searching for. The API will return all stars whose name contains it.

request.description:
# star

This API provides data of all stars. It contains 10 parameters, and the request needs to have at least one of them.

The request has to contain one of the above parameters at least.

query.description: This represents the index of the page being returned
This represents the data of the moons returning per page

request.description:
This API returns information about the moon. It takes in two parameters. There are three circumstances:

- If either of the parameters is none, it returns all data.
- If both of the parameters are passed in, it returns the data by page.

response.name: all_moons

query.description: This represents the index of the page being returned
This represents the data of the planets returning per page

request.description:
This API returns information about the planets. It takes in two parameters. There are three circumstances:

- If either of the parameters is none, it returns all data.
- If both of the parameters are passed in, it returns the data by page.

query.description: This represents the index of the page being returned
This represents the data of the stars returning per page

request.description:
This API returns information about the stars. It takes in two parameters. There are three circumstances:

- If either of the parameters is none, it returns all data.
- If both of the parameters are passed in, it returns the data by page.
